BUGGYCOMMIT.MESSAGE: Esql refactor date tests (#117923) This refactors a bit of the type logic in the parametrized testing to pass the input values as java Instants for millisecond and nanosecond date. Mainly, this impacts verifier functions. The goal here is to ensure that the values are correctly converted based on the type they were generated as, rather than relying on the verifier function to know how to convert from a long with no additional information. This will make tests that have mixed millisecond and nanosecond inputs easier to write correctly.
